        " ICP-MS , etc. have benefited from the unique quality of this technology, that is barely 42 years old. The power of time resolved analysis can not be overstated. It has stimulated the development new and exciting tools for research as varied as geochemistry and forensic chemistry; biochemistry and oceanography. Additionally, increases in sample throughput from dozens of samples a day to hundreds of samples a day has revolutionized environmental analysis, reducing costs. Fundamentally, this is all due to the fact that while the sample sits at environmental pressure, the analyzer and detector is at 42/42,42 of that same pressure during normal operation.     An inductively coupled plasma for spectrometry is sustained in a torch that consists of three concentric tubes, usually made of ": null
    },
    {
        "quartz": "quartz"
    },
    {
        ", although the inner tube can be sapphire if hydrofluoric acid is being used. The end of this torch is placed inside an induction coil supplied with a radio-frequency electric current. A flow of ": null
