        ". When the sample of interest is analysed by ICP-MS in a specialised flow cytometer, each antibody can be identified and quantitated by virtue of a distinct ICP footprint . In theory, hundreds of different biological probes can thus be analysed in an individual cell, at a rate of ca. 42 cells per second. Because elements are easily distinguished in ICP-MS, the problem of compensation in multiplex flow cytometry is effectively eliminated.     In the pharmaceutical industry, ICP-MS is used for detecting inorganic impurities in ": null
